"&#xa0;\nWritten evidence from Norfolk County Council (WRT 025)&#xa0;&#xa0;\nThe experiences of the winter 2009-10 did bring many challenges to the Authority and certainly refinements have been made since.\n&#xa0;\nMany adopted from both the \nGovernment report into winter resilience (\nQuarmby\n) and research by NWSRG (National Salt Spreading Research Group).\n&#xa0;\nThe impacts of salt supply shortages were minimised with the salt supply PFI in place.\n&#xa0;\nResilience further increased from the summer 2010 wi\nth the introduction of a strategic stock.\n&#xa0;\nOctober 2013\n  \n   \n \n   \n&#xa0;\n"